body:
## Bevy version
Bevy 0.15.3
Also reproduced on 0.16.0-rc1 and main

## Relevant system information
```ignore
2025-03-21T01:30:21.231373Z  INFO bevy_render::renderer: AdapterInfo { name: "AMD Radeon RX 7900 XTX", vendor: 4098, device: 29772, device_type: DiscreteGpu, driver: "AMD proprietary driver", driver_info: "24.12.1 (LLPC)", backend: Vulkan }
```

## What you did
Run the following example and press the A key on your keyboard:
```
use bevy::prelude::*;

fn main() {
    App::new()
        .add_plugins(DefaultPlugins)
        .add_systems(Startup, setup_scene)
        .add_systems(Update, remove_first_strong_handle)
        .run();
}

#[derive(Component)]
struct FirstStrongHandle;

fn setup_scene(
    mut commands: Commands,
    mut meshes: ResMut<Assets<Mesh>>,
    mut materials: ResMut<Assets<StandardMaterial>>,
) {
    let mesh = meshes.add(Cuboid::new(1.0, 1.0, 1.0));
    let material = materials.add(StandardMaterial {
        base_color: Color::srgb_u8(255, 0, 0),
        ..Default::default()
    });

    commands.spawn((
        Mesh3d(mesh.clone()),
        MeshMaterial3d(material.clone()),
        Transform::from_translation(Vec3::new(1.0, 0.0, -4.0)),
        FirstStrongHandle,
    ));

    commands.spawn((
        Mesh3d(mesh),
        MeshMaterial3d(materials.get_strong_handle(material.id()).unwrap()),
        Transform::from_translation(Vec3::new(-1.0, 0.0, -4.0)),
    ));

    commands.spawn(Camera3d::default());
}

fn remove_first_strong_handle(
    mut commands: Commands,
    input: Res<ButtonInput<KeyCode>>,
    query: Query<Entity, With<FirstStrongHandle>>,
) {
    if input.just_pressed(KeyCode::KeyA) {
        commands.entity(query.single()).despawn(); // Need an `.unwrap()` after `.single()` if testing on 0.16.0-rc1 or main
    }
}
```

## What went wrong
Only the first entity with the material handle is despawned however the second cube also disappears.

Before pressing A:
![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a4b2179a-5527-4651-96b9-e7159eb33fd9)

After pressing A:
![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/30c24690-bb60-431a-bfb0-0c53f155680f)

## Additional information
Discord message with where this is most likely happening: https://discord.com/channels/691052431525675048/866787577687310356/1352445303550382194

> quick question related to this material issue I was experiencing. At the bottom of track_assets, AssetEvent::Unused is queued and there is a call to remove_dropped(). However, in remove_dropped() the asset isn't dropped if there's duplicate handles but AssetEvent::Unused is still queued. I also see that in extract_render_asset() the asset id is inserted into a removed hashset. Shouldn't this only be done if AssetEvent::Removed is fired? Or on the other side, don't queue AssetEvent::Unused unless there's 0 duplicate handles (as remove_dropped() checks for)?
